    "Then since z ′ = z ∧ y *, we have xR i u ≬ y *, which contradicts the fact that R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y.Recall from Fact 4.42.2 that a principal frame is R-tight iff it is strong.",
    "For lattice-complete principal frames, we can add the following observation concerning R-tightness.Fact 4.48 (R-tight and R-princ).",
    "If F is a lattice-complete principal possi- bility frame, then F satisfies the R-tight condition iff F satisfies the R-princ condition from § 4.4: R i (x) is a principal downset if R i (x) ̸ = ∅.",
    "From left to right, assuming F satisfies R-tight and R i (x) ̸ = ∅, we show that R i (x) = ↓ R i (x), where is the join operation in the complete Boolean lattice minus ⊥ that underlies F.By Fact 4.34.1, R-tight implies R-down, so R i (x) is a downset.",
    "Thus, to show that R i (x) = ↓ R i (x), it suffices to show that R i (x) ∈ R i (x)."
